cs.CV, cs.IR, cs.MM, cs.CL, cs.DC 

The paper discusses the implementation of a large-scale visual search system and its impact on user engagement, which suggests that it could fall under several sub-categories. 

cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on visual search and content recommendation. 

cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is also likely as the paper discusses the use of search algorithms and recommendation systems. 

cs.MM (Multimedia) is another possible category as the paper deals with visual content and its organization. 

cs.CL (Computation and Language) could be relevant as the paper discusses natural language processing and text-based search. 

cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is also possible as the paper discusses the use of distributed computation platforms like Amazon Web Services.
